Loose substrate doesn’t have to be scary or controversial. My dragons have lived 2, 3 and 5 years without it because I was misinformed about lose substrate. They would be okay without it, but if it enriches their life, why not? Never use just sand alone, you want to mix it with organic top soil and bake it at 250 for 30 mins. #beardeddragon #reptiletips #substrate #enrichmentforpets #lizardsofinstagram

Brumation! Another subject that has soo much conflicting information. People say to offer salads to your bearded dragons during this time, but that just doesn’t make any sense to me because they are not basking, warming, or digesting during this time. Do offer them fresh water. You can turn your heat lamp off and just do UV if you want to, but during this time lights are not necessary. Do your own research and do whays best for you and your pets. Hope this helps a little. #beardeddragon #brumation #beardietips #hibernation

Is the headbobbing just Chuck trying to set boundaries? #headbob #noboundaries #love

Headbobbing comes in many forms and means many things. People always go straight to “bad things”. Headbobbing is a form of communication and 
sometimes they’re mad, sometimes they’re happy. We don’t always know Chuck’s reason for head bobbing but we base it on the situation. Here, he might be saying “yes! I love hornworms! Give me more!” Beardies are unique and have massive personalities, we are learning more now than ever, so stay open minded and don’t judge people without the facts. Sorry for the not so great quality, this video came from his enclosure camera. #headbob #beardeddragon
